{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "acc8d07c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# PW3: Mice's sleep stages classification with MLP\n",
    "\n",
    "Group:\n",
    "\n",
    "- David Schildböck\n",
    "- Kénan Augsburger\n",
    "\n",
    "Goals:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Prepare and pre-process the available data to train a neural-network for solving a classification task.\n",
    "- Design experiments to exploit the available data to come up with an automatic classification system.\n",
    "- Design, train and evaluate neural networks (Multi-Layer Perceptron) to solve a real-world problem.\n",
    "- Perform hyper-parameter tuning to find an appropriate neural network architecture and to achieve a good performing model.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "51362639",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introduction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "b1ca0b0d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Basic imports\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from tqdm.notebook import tqdm\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Setting up the visualisation style\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d1e44c55",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Training data:\n",
    "\n",
    "- EEG_mouse_data_1.csv (same mouse as PW1)\n",
    "- EEG_mouse_data_2.csv (another mouse for training)\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: if you want to concatenate pandas dataframes, you can do it with « pd.concat »."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "d29f3488",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_train_data_1 = pd.read_csv(\"pw3_data/EEG_mouse_data_1.csv\")\n",
    "raw_train_data_2 = pd.read_csv(\"pw3_data/EEG_mouse_data_2.csv\")\n",
    "raw_train_data = pd.concat([raw_train_data_1, raw_train_data_2], ignore_index=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8cd523dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Testing data:\n",
    "\n",
    "- EEG_mouse_data_test.csv (another mouse for testing)\n",
    "\n",
    "All of these mice are genetical clones of each other so the data will be slightly different from\n",
    "mouse to mouse but will still be similar.  \n",
    "We don't provide any notebook. You can use code of previous practical works to help you. You\n",
    "can choose whether you want to do it on Colab or not.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "085c1feb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_test_data = pd.read_csv(\"pw3_data/EEG_mouse_data_test.csv\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "da96b96b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
